HEADWORD: Diaster
<hw>Di*as"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk>
= <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ star.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
double star; -- applied to the nucleus of a cell, when, during cell
division, the loops of the nuclear network separate into two groups,
preparatory to the formation of two daughter nuclei. See
<er>Karyokinesis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diastole</ent>⟦br⟧
